The Joburg Zoo has extended the validation of tickets that expired during the hard lockdown restrictions. To speak about that and how the industry has been doing since the relaxations of rules, eNCA's Duduzile Ramela speaks to MMC for Community Development, Margaret Arnolds. JOHANNESBURG - The Joburg Zoo has extended the validation of tickets that expired during the hard lockdown. These only apply to tickets bought just before the country entered level five lockdown in March. The extension is valid until the end of October.